   "SSExactMajority/Convergence/DecisionReach.lean:27:0: The module doc-string for a file should be the first command after the imports.\nPlease, add a module doc-string before `/-- Decision-phase reachability via the **macro-step** variant. -/\ntheorem decision_reaches_consensus_of_macroStep [Inhabited (Fin n ├Ś Fin n)] {trank Rmax : ŌäĢ}\n    {rankDelta : AgentState n ├Ś AgentState n ŌåÆ AgentState n ├Ś AgentState n}\n    (hMacro :\n      ŌłĆ C : Config (AgentState n) Opinion n,\n        InSswap C ŌåÆ\n          0 < wrongAnswerCount C ŌåÆ\n            Ōłā (╬│ : DetScheduler n) (k : ŌäĢ),\n              InSswap (execution (protocolPEM n trank Rmax rankDelta) C ╬│ k) Ōł¦\n                wrongAnswerCount (execution (protocolPEM n trank Rmax rankDelta) C ╬│ k) < wrongAnswerCount C) :\n    ŌłĆ C : Config (AgentState n) Opinion n,\n      InSswap C ŌåÆ\n        Ōłā (╬│ : DetScheduler n) (t : ŌäĢ), IsConsensusConfig (execution (protocolPEM n trank Rmax rankDelta) C ╬│ t) :=\n  by\n  intro C hC\n  obtain Ō¤©╬│, t, hC_t, h0_tŌ¤® :=\n    reach_zero_potential_macro (P := protocolPEM n trank Rmax rankDelta) (Pinv := InSswap) (Žå := wrongAnswerCount)\n      hMacro C hC\n  exact Ō¤©╬│, t, isConsensusConfig_of_InSswap_of_wrongAnswerCount_zero hC_t h0_tŌ¤®`.\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Convergence/DecisionReach.lean:2:18: * '. All rights reserved.':\n'Copyright (c) YYYY' should be followed by a space\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Convergence/DecisionReach.lean:4:0: * '\n# Decision-Phase Reachability via Single-Step Reduction\n\n`hDecisionPhase` reduced to a single local hypothesis using the\n\"wrong answer count\" potential ŌĆö the number of agents whose `.answer`\nfield disagrees with the global majority.\n\nWhen the count is zero (all answers correct), an `InSswap`\nconfiguration is precisely an `IsConsensusConfig` (since `Stim = Sswap Ōł® Sout`).\n\nThe local single-step hypothesis requires showing that from any\n`InSswap` configuration with at least one wrong answer there exists an\ninteraction `(u, v)` that preserves `InSswap` (or, more generally,returns to it after a finite number of steps via a reset cycle) while\ndecreasing the wrong-answer count.  The paper's Lemma 11 provides the\nprobabilistic version of this; the deterministic discharge requires\ncareful timer/reset management.':\nIf an authors line spans multiple lines, each line but the last must end with a trailing comma\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Convergence/DecisionReach.lean:4:0: * '\n# Decisi':\nThe authors line should begin with 'Authors: '\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
